item.title: Dynamic and automated dashboard (Excel or BI) for stock market transactions - Upwork
item.description:
Hello
I am looking to seek services of an advanced level MS Excel, Power Query and Power BI expert. Basically I frequently trade in stock market and I have trade confirmations in the form of PDF files. I want to develop a Dashboard and automate my record of transactions related to stock market so that I don’t need to manually maintain any record. Snapshots of my requirement is as below:
1. Develop an automated and fully dynamic dashboard (either in excel of using BI, I don’t mind that). The dashboard must show all the time:
a. Cumulative realized gain/losses of my transaction (month wise and year wise)
b. Cumulative unrealized gain/losses at any point in time
c. Quantities and cost of unsold shares at any point in time
d. Automation of above record through Power Query or Power BI so that I simply place new transaction files in the folder and my whole record get update through one link.
Notes:
I need to implement a to c through First-in-First-out method. I can explain this at a later stage once anybody shows willingness to do this work.
I am open to mutually agree a fair reimbursement of the efforts anybody would be required to deploy. However, the amount would only be payable upon development of a successful model. The bidder can show me the model online on his/her screen and once I am satisfied, we can move for delivery and payment.
I can share the record of transactions once anybody shows willingness to take this project.
Thanks
Kr
Kamran

Budget: $100

item.title: Data Analytics Manager for an Immigration Law Firm - Upwork
item.description:
Data Analytics Manager - Looking for an exciting opportunity?

We're seeking a dynamic Data Analytics Manager to lead a talented team of data analysts. You'll be at the forefront of utilizing cutting-edge tools such as Salesforce for reporting and dashboards, Azure Data Factory for managing connections to our SQL data warehouse, and Power BI for data visualization. This role calls for strong leadership, technical prowess, and a strategic mindset to drive successful data analytics projects that directly impact our business goals.
Join us and be part of something big!

Key Responsibilities:
•     Lead, mentor, and develop a team of data analysts, fostering a collaborative and high-performance culture.
•     Oversee the design, implementation, and maintenance of data analytics projects, ensuring they align with business objectives.
•     Utilize Salesforce for reporting and dashboards to provide insights into business operations and performance.
•     Manage data pipelines using Azure Data Factory to connect various data sources to our SQL data warehouse.
•     Develop and maintain Power BI dashboards and reports to communicate findings to stakeholders.
•     Ensure the accuracy, completeness, and reliability of data through effective data governance and quality control processes.
•     Collaborate with stakeholders to identify data requirements and deliver insights that drive business strategies.
•     Stay updated on the latest trends and technologies in data analytics and integrate best practices into the team's processes.
•     Manage project timelines, resources, and budgets effectively to meet deadlines and deliver high-quality results.

Qualifications:
•     Bachelor’s degree in Data Science, Statistics, Computer Science, or a related field; a Master’s degree is a plus.
•     5+ years of experience in data analytics, with at least 2 years in a leadership or management role.
•     Proficiency in Salesforce reporting and dashboards.
•     Experience with Azure Data Factory for managing data pipelines and connections to SQL data warehouses.
•     Proficiency in Power BI for data visualization.
•     Strong understanding of SQL and data modeling techniques.
•     Excellent problem-solving skills and the ability to translate complex data into actionable insights.
•     Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to interact effectively with stakeholders at all levels.
•     Demonstrated experience managing and mentoring a team.
•     Strong organizational skills and attention to detail.


We offer more than just an opportunity to make a difference. At this Firm we care about our team members, work hard to provide a great culture, and keep our whole firm connected so that we remain close, even if separated by distance. And we have FUN while changing LIVES.  Join us now and be a part of our exciting journey!

Hourly Range: $15.00-$20.00

We are seeking an experienced and knowledgeable Training Instructor to lead our "Advanced Data Analysis with Power BI" course that will be held in Malaysia. The ideal candidate will possess in-depth expertise in Power BI, SQL, and advanced data analysis techniques, and have a strong background in business intelligence and data visualization. The instructor will be responsible for delivering high-quality training sessions, engaging with participants, and ensuring a comprehensive understanding of the course material.

Key Responsibilities:

Deliver and facilitate the "Advanced Data Analysis with Power BI" training course according to the provided outline.
Instruct participants on advanced Power BI techniques, including data modeling, DAX, data transformation, and visualization.
Guide participants through practical exercises and lab sessions to reinforce learning.
Provide insights on integrating SQL with Power BI for data extraction and analysis.
Teach advanced analytical techniques such as time intelligence, forecasting, and anomaly detection.
Ensure participants can optimize performance in Power BI, including model optimization and performance improvement.
Assist participants in creating and managing dashboards, reports, and paginated reports.
Share best practices for data visualization and effective report design.
Manage and troubleshoot issues related to Power BI, including data connectivity and security.
Evaluate participants' progress and provide feedback and support as needed.


Qualifications:
Proven experience in teaching or training on Power BI and SQL.
Extensive knowledge of data analysis, data modeling, and data visualization using Power BI.
Strong understanding of DAX and advanced data transformation techniques.
Experience with integrating SQL databases with Power BI.
Familiarity with real-time dashboarding and advanced analytics involving data science.
Excellent communication and presentation skills.
Ability to engage and motivate participants with varying levels of experience.
Relevant certifications in Power BI or data analysis are highly desirable.
